  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDE UK Organisational Development Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">International Development Enterprises - UK (IDE-UK) is part of the IDE International family. Since 2003 it has been supporting its international country offices in work that seeks to increase the incomes of poor farmers, strengthen co-operative structures, innovate with new irrigation technologies and improve access to new markets. After a successful start based on funding from DfID, in 2007 the founder left and IDE-UK contracted substantially. An organisational review was undertaken in 2008, which resulted in an organisational strategy (2009-2013). The key focus of the strategy is on improving the funding base and reducing reliance on project overheads/administration budgets to fund core costs. Financial management upgrades and capacity to influence UK and international policy debates are also important objectives. The thrust of this application is to enable IDE-UK to strengthen the role of Trustees and staff leadership to drive the implementation of the strategy. If this is successful the organisation will be able to broaden its funding sources, increase its visibility and influence and reach its goal of doubling income for 250,000 poor rural households.</narrative>
  </description>
